scheduled_maintenances.name: Announcing IP Address Changes (No Operational Impact)

incident_updates.body:
We will be reducing the number of Zoom CDN ranges to 4 IPv4 ranges and 4 IPv6 ranges, all of which are already in use. 4164 IPv4 ranges will be removed from Zoom resources starting no earlier than 30 days from the posting of this notice. We recommend that network administrators, with Zoom specific firewall or network rules, update their systems as soon as possible in preparation.

See a list of the 4164 IPv4 subnet ranges that have been removed from Zooms CDN: https://assets.zoom.us/docs/ipranges/ZoomCDN-September2023.txt

For a list of all CDN IP ranges, see the following:
IPv4: https://assets.zoom.us/docs/ipranges/ZoomCDN.txt
IPv6: https://assets.zoom.us/docs/ipranges/ZoomCDN-IPv6.txt

Additionally, the following data center is no longer in use and will be removed from Zoom resources starting no earlier than 30 days from the posting of this notice. 

Removed data center: 
sx.zoom.us

A complete list of network firewall IP ranges for Zoom can be found on the Zoom Support site at: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/201362683

scheduled_maintenances.name: Scheduled Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Update (11/4/2023)

incident_updates.body:
Zoom will be enforcing a new minimum version of all our Zoom clients and plugins, roughly 90 days from now on November 4, 2023. This affects the following products: 
 - Zoom client for meetings (Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, Blackberry, and Intune)
 - Zoom Rooms (including Zoom Room Controllers) 
 - Zoom Phone Appliances
 - Outlook Plug-in
 - Browser Scheduler Extensions
 - VDI Client and Plugin
 - Virtual Room Connector
 - Meetings Connector
 - Recording Connector
 - Meeting SDK
 - Video SDK
 - Zoom Contact Center SDK (Native)
 - Zoom Node
 - Zoom Phone Local Survivability (ZPLS) module

Please ensure your devices are updated to the latest version. 

For more information, such as specific versions we are enforcing, please see the Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Policy support article: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/360059429231 

To assist with checking the client versions on your account, refer to the Dashboard support article for more information: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/360039656511#h_13ce9a73-91e5-4df6-9cb5-c815b1605cf5

scheduled_maintenances.name: Blocking of Non-10DLC Registered SMS Traffic

incident_updates.body: Scheduled maintenance is currently in progress. We will provide updates as necessary.

Starting July 23, Zoom will be blocking SMS traffic from US and Canada toll numbers not attached to a 10DLC Brand and Campaign. If you are experiencing SMS service disruption, create a 10DLC Brand and Campaign to resolve the issue. Details are available in this support article: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/5016496738445-SMS-MMS-10DLC-Compliance-for-Zoom-Phone-and-Zoom-Contact-Center
